s have time recharm my pet and get him back on the mob.  The one thing you do want to do is when the mob enrages guard your pet (I do hope you have Pet Control) and wait for the enrage to end then hit the mob with one small nuke I use a nuke band (5 damage) then finish it with your pet that way you get full exp.  So any ways that is my exp with charm it is a very powerful spell (have been able to do the named giants with nothing more then me and a cleric)  But it is very very risky you will die and die many times there is no way around that.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarelorn>Sarelorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 9:52:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1832.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I then park the pet in a nice little corner and pull mobs to it useing a debuff (you do not I repeat do not want to do damage to said mob)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Pick up a white ceramic band to pull with. 5 points of damage isn't enough to make the mob summon, and it counts as damage to keep the pet from getting the majority of the xp. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3284">Sarelorn Stonecaller</a><BR>
